=See this also in Mediawiki - <a href="http://response.commonaccord.org/01/Agt/Type/Privacy/Common/Form_T01_V01">response.commonaccord.org</a>
=At the recent "Road Ahead" Program presented by the MIT SENSEable City Lab (<a href="http://senseable.mit.edu/roadahead/"> senseable.mit.edu/roadahead</a>), it was obvious that the lack of societal (and inter-societal) agreement on the scope of permitted use of information about people and communities (privacy) was a pervasive issue.  We float the idea that a "model" privacy policy expressed in componentized format (source) could help move along the discussion if it was used as a resource for companies to create their policies and as a target for discussion.  This fits with and can help drive the patient Consents project.

=This also appears at <a href="https://github.com/CommonAccord/commonaccord/tree/master/Doc/01/Agt/Type/Privacy/Common/Form_T01_V01"> Github</a> where it can be forked, and on the site at  <a href="http://commonaccord.org/index.php?action=source&file=/01/Agt/Type/Privacy/Common/ Form_T01_V01">commonaccord.org/</a>
